    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Talking About Race</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Sarah Brockus letter on July 16 issue about race relations holds real discussion could begin if all people were to admit they are a little bit racist9</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>We are all a little bit racist -- from Dominicans to light-skinned blacks to Chinese to rednecks. If we can just come to the plate admitting that then the real discussion can begin.</p>
        <p>Sarah Brockus  New York</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
